<div class="title">
<h5>
<a href="/bringing-characters-to-life">
Bringing Characters to Life<br>
</a> </h5>
<div class="tagline">
<a href="/bringing-characters-to-life">
More than just code and wires.
</a> </div>
<div class="author">by
<a href="/users/pburgess">
<span class="name">Phillip Burgess</span>
</a> </div>
</div>
</div>
<a href="/bringing-characters-to-life">
<img src='https://cdn-learn.adafruit.com/guides/images/000/001/236/medium310/thumbnail.jpg?1454736495' class='img-responsive guide-image' data-standard-image='https://cdn-learn.adafruit.com/guides/images/000/001/236/medium310/thumbnail.jpg?1454736495' data-mobile-image='https://cdn-learn.adafruit.com/guides/images/000/001/236/medium800/thumbnail.jpg?1454736495' />
</a> <div class="details">
<div class="description">
<a href="/bringing-characters-to-life">
Whether robots, animatronics or purely onscreen avatars, how your creation looks and moves will make or break an emotional connection with your audience. Will they regard it as believable and “alive,” or a dull and obvious assemblage of mechanisms and software?
</a> </div>
</div>
</div>
